Class Player

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.PSP034.model.Player
public class Player
extends Object
Represents an active player in a given game.

  • Constructor Details

    • Player

      public Player​(String name, PlayerColor color)
      Creates a new Player class instantiating a structure for Workers (that needs to be initialized using addWorker(Sex, Tile)). At the time of instantiation, there is no myGod associated, which has to bet set using setMyGod(GodsRules).
      Parameters:
      name - Player's name.
      color - Player's color.

  • Method Details

    • hasLost

      public boolean hasLost()
      Returns if a player has lost (and has to be eliminated by class contract).
      Returns:
      true if the player has lost, false otherwise.

    • setHasLost

      public void setHasLost​(boolean hasLost)
      Flags a losing player.
      Parameters:
      hasLost - true if the player has lost, false otherwise.

    • addWorker

      public void addWorker​(Sex sex, Tile myTile)
      Creates a new Worker associated to the Player, given color, sex and player name. Places the Worker in its starting Tile.
      Parameters:
      sex - Worker's sex.
      myTile - Starting worker tile.

    • getMyWorkers
